Privacy Policy of StudyTok
Welcome to StudyTok! This Privacy Policy explains our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of your information through the StudyTok app. By using our services, you consent to the practices described in this policy.
1. Information We Collect
- Personal Information: When you register for an account, we collect personal information such as your name, email address, and password.
- Usage: We collect information on how you interact with our app, including features used, frequency of use, and time spent on the app.
- Device Information: We gather information about the devices you use to access our app, such as hardware models, operating system, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information.
- Cookies and Tracking Technologies: We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance user experience, analyze usage, and improve service efficiency. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.
2. How We Use Your Information
- Service Provision: We use your information to provide, maintain, and improve our app and services.
- Communication: We may use your contact information to send you updates, newsletters, and promotional offers. You can opt-out of marketing communications at any time.
- Analytics and Improvement: We analyze usage data to understand user behavior and preferences, enabling us to enhance our app’s functionality and user experience.
3. Sharing of Your Information
- Third-Party Sharing: We may share your information with trusted third parties to facilitate advertising services. These parties are obligated to protect your information.
- Legal Obligations: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., court orders).
4. Your Rights
- Access and Update: You have the right to access and update your personal information through your account settings.
- Data Deletion: You can request to delete your personal information, and deactivating your account will also remove your user-generated content from our app.
- Data Portability: You may request a copy of your personal information in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.
5. Data Security
- Data Storage: We utilize Google Firebase for secure data storage and management.
- Security Measures: We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, please understand that no security system is infallible.
6. International Transfers
- Global Processing: Your information may be processed and stored in countries around the world, including those with different data protection laws. We ensure that such transfers are in compliance with applicable legal requirements.
7. Changes to This Policy
- Policy Updates: We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any significant changes will be communicated through the app or via email. Please review this policy periodically for updates.
8. Contact Us
- Questions and Concerns: If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
info@studytok.com
or
support@studytok.com
.
